<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.D2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 2 COMMENCEMENT OF PROCEEDINGS [rr 3&#x2013;6]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.D2" type="ext"/>DIVISION 2</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">COMMENCEMENT OF PROCEEDINGS [rr 3&#x2013;6]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78 r 3] r 3 Publication of notice of intended application for probate or administration: section 42 of P&amp;A Act ">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78 r 3]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Publication of notice of intended application for probate or administration: section 42 of P&amp;A Act </title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>3</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<glp:note>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF" type="legref"><ci:content>(cf former Part 78, rule 10)</ci:content></ci:cite></text></p></glp:note>
</leg:bodytext>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The notice of an intended application for the grant of probate or administration that is required under section 42 of the Probate and Administration Act 1898 must be published on the New South Wales Online Registry website.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The notice must include:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the date of any will (and of any codicil to any such will) that is sought to be proved or, if the will bears no date, a statement of that fact and of the will&#x2019;s approximate date, if known, and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.2.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>a statement requiring creditors of the deceased to send in their claims.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subrule (2) does not apply to the grant of administration under section 91 of the Succession Act 2006.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Court may require further advertisement of the intended application.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R3.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_SC.SGM_UCPN.SC.78-3-1" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78.3.1] Approved form"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.78-3-1" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78.3.1] </edpnum><title>Approved form</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The approved form for a Notice of intended application for a grant of probate or administration is UCPR Form 116.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_SC.SGM_UCPN.SC.78-3-2" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78.3.2] Publication of notices of intention to apply">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [SCR Pt 78.3.2] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1898-13" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Wills, Probate and Administration Act 1898</remotelink> s 42.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_REG_1970-1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Supreme Court Rules 1970</remotelink> Pt 78 r 17(2).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.78-3-2" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78.3.2] </edpnum><title>Publication of notices of intention to apply</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Notices of intention to apply for probate or administration must be published in the manner prescribed by the rules: Probate and Administration Act 1898 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="0099" refpt="WPN.PAA.WPAN.S42" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 42</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
. (The section was amended in September 2012 to remove the previous requirement for newspaper advertisement.) The present rule applies to intended proceedings after 21 January 2013 and requires, instead of newspaper advertisement, that all notices of intention to apply for probate, administration or a reseal to the Supreme Court must be advertised via the NSW Online Registry website.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The court may require further advertisement of an intended application.</text></p>
<p>
<text>Prior notice of an application may be dispensed with in cases of extreme urgency: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1922"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr002753" spanref="cr002753-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="SRNSW"/><ci:volume num="22"/><ci:page num="227"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr002754" spanref="cr002754-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WNNSW"/><ci:volume num="39"/><ci:page num="41"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Estate of Pickles</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr002753-001" status="unval">(1922) 22 SR (NSW) 227</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr002754-002" status="unval">39 WN (NSW) 41a</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="70385" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1911"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr002755" spanref="cr002755-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="12"/><ci:page num="310"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr002756" spanref="cr002756-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="17"/><ci:page num="350"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr002757" spanref="cr002757-003"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC1100030"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Greenway v McKay</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr002755-001" status="unval">(1911) 12 CLR 310</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr002756-002" status="unval">17 ALR 350</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr002757-003"> BC1100030</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="62261" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
<p>
<text>The advertisement or publication of an application for the grant of probate to one of two executors named in the will must mention the second executor and state the intention to apply for probate with leave reserved for that person to join the applicant as executor: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1865"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr002758" spanref="cr002758-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="SCRNSWEq"/><ci:volume num="4"/><ci:page num="16"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">In the Goods of Simonds</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr002758-001" status="unval">(1865) 4 SCR (NSW) Eq 16</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. That notice must be served on the other person: see SCR 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R17.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Pt 78 r 17(2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_SC.SGM_UCPN.SC.78-3-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78.3.5] NSW Online Registry"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.78-3-5" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78.3.5] </edpnum><title>NSW Online Registry</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The NSW Online Registry website (
<remotelink href="www.onlineregistry.lawlink.nsw.gov.au" hrefclass="http" newwindow="YES">http://www.onlineregistry.lawlink.nsw.gov.au</remotelink>
) provides online registry services for the Supreme Court, District Court and Local Court. All notices of intention to apply for probate, administration or a reseal to the Supreme Court are required to be published on the online registry website.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78 r 4] r 4 Publication of notice of intended application for reseal of foreign grant: section 109 of P&amp;A Act">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78 r 4]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Publication of notice of intended application for reseal of foreign grant: section 109 of P&amp;A Act</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>4</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<glp:note>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF" type="legref"><ci:content>(cf former Part 78, rule 10)</ci:content></ci:cite></text></p></glp:note>
<l><li id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4.1"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4.1" type="ext"/>(1)</lilabel>
<p><text>The notice of an intended application for the resealing of a foreign grant that is required under section 109 of the Probate and Administration Act 1898 must be published on the New South Wales Online Registry website.</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4.2"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4.2" type="ext"/>(2)</lilabel>
<p><text>The Court may require further advertisement of the intended application.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT78.R4.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_SC.SGM_UCPN.SC.78-4-1" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 78.4.1] Approved form"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.78-4-1" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 78.4.1] </edpnum><title>Approved form</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The approved form for a Notice of intended application for probate, administration or reseal is UCPR Form 116.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
